<p><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-2716" src="https://www.oregonmotorcyclerental.com/newsite/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-300x169.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="169" srcset="../../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-300x169.jpg 300w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-768x432.jpg 768w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-260x146.jpg 260w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-50x28.jpg 50w, ../../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/brake-1-1-133x75.jpg 133w" sizes="(max-width:767px) 300px, 300px" />Hey world, it&#8217;s no secret, I&#8217;m a fan of the LHRB system. With the yeatts perch, just about anyone can set things up to use both, at the same time. Really. The new short lever from Mountain Engineering gives true 1-finger braking, and with a short clutch lever, both are in play. Ballistic engine clutching is what I needed to put my personal steed, back to factory performance, and still ride the way I want. Play with the lever positioning and see for yourself. Cheers</p>
